(firstQuint)Effect of Hypertonic Solutions on Allergic Rhinitis Patients.

 The medical records of the patients who admitted to outpatient clinic of otorhinolaryngology department of a tertiary referral center were retrospectively investigated.

 The symptom scores and nasal eosinophil levels of the patients were recorded.

 Patients using hypertonic solutions alone or steroid nasal spray alone were compared.

